SIMPLE: unappropriated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unappropriated
<hw>Un`ap*pro"pri*a`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>appropriated</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Not specially appropriate; having no special application.</def>
<rj><au>J. Warton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not granted to any person, corporation, or the like,
to the exclusion of others; <as>as, <ex>unappropriated</ex>
lands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not granted for, or applied to, any specific
purpose; <as>as, the <ex>unappropriated</ex> moneys in the
treasury</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note> In the proceedings of the United States congress, money for
specific purposes must first be authorized by law, and must subsequently
be appropriated in a separate action. Money authorized but not
appropriated may be described as <ex>unappropriated</ex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unapproved</ent>⟦br⟧
